abstract: Sen Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts delivers opening night keynote speech at Democratic National Convention following day of protests against Hillary Clinton from supporters of Sen Bernie Sanders of Vermont; Warren's call for Clinton nomination focuses on indictment of Republican rival Donald Trump's business record and economic message, portraying him as epitome of 1 percent who brought so many young voters into Sanders's camp.
lead_paragraph: The Massachusetts senator issued an implicit warning to supporters of Senator Bernie Sanders that not voting for Mrs. Clinton could put Donald J. Trump in the White House.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Urges Liberals to Vote for Hillary Clinton
headline.print_headline: Warren Urges Liberals to Embrace Clinton Bid
